The paper discusses structured sensing matrices in compressed sensing, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also mentions the advantages of structured sensing matrices in terms of hardware implementation, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different structured sensing matrices in terms of signal recovery, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV).
